</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">c</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Ω</span> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/NNReal/Defs.html#NNReal\">NNReal</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">fs_lim</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">ω</span> : <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Tendsto\">Filter.Tendsto</a> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">fs</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">ω</span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhds\">nhds</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">ω</span>)</span>)</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Tendsto\">Filter.Tendsto</a> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Lebesgue/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.lintegral\">∫⁻</a> (<span class=\"fn\">ω</span> : <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span>)<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Lebesgue/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.lintegral\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">fs</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">ω</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Lebesgue/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.lintegral\">∂</a><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">μ</span></span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhds\">nhds</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Lebesgue/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.lintegral\">∫⁻</a> (<span class=\"fn\">ω</span> : <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span>)<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Lebesgue/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.lintegral\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">ω</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Lebesgue/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.lintegral\">∂</a><span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">μ</span></span>)</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A bounded convergence theorem for a finite measure:\nIf a sequence of bounded continuous non-negative functions are uniformly bounded by a constant\nand tend pointwise to a limit, then their integrals (`MeasureTheory.lintegral`) against the finite\nmeasure tend to the integral of the limit.\n\nA related result with more general assumptions is\n`MeasureTheory.tendsto_lintegral_nn_filter_of_le_const`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/FiniteMeasure.html#MeasureTheory.FiniteMeasure.tendsto_lintegral_nn_of_le_const","kind":"theorem","line":634,"name":"MeasureTheory.FiniteMeasure.tendsto_lintegral_nn_of_le_const","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/FiniteMeasure.lean#L634-L648"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/FiniteMeasure.html#MeasureTheory.FiniteMeasure.t2Space\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">FiniteMeasure</span>.<span class=\"name\">t2Space</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">Ω</span> : <a hr